  "prompt": "Where can I download free pdf books for mechanical engineering?",
  "response": "There are several online resources where you can find free PDF books on mechanical engineering. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **Project Gutenberg**: Although primarily focused on classic literature, you might find some textbooks and reference materials related to engineering.\n\n2. **Open Library**: Part of the Internet Archive, Open Library offers a wide range of books, including some on engineering topics, available for borrowing or download.\n\n3. **Google Books**: While not all books are available for full view or download, Google Books can be a good resource for accessing parts of books and discovering where to find them.\n\n4. **Bookboon**: Specializes in providing free textbooks for students, including several on mechanical engineering topics.\n\n5. **ResearchGate**: A platform where researchers share papers and publications. You may find engineering books or articles available for free.\n\n6. **MIT OpenCourseWare**: Offers free course materials, including lecture notes and textbooks, from a range of MIT's engineering courses.\n\n7. **Scribd**: Offers a wide range of books, and they have a free 30-day trial that you could use to access some engineering books.\n\n8. **Library Genesis (LibGen)**: Offers a vast collection of books across various disciplines, including mechanical engineering. Be cautious about legality and copyright when using this resource.\n\n9. **PDF Drive**: A free search engine which allows you to search, preview, and download millions of PDF files into your devices.\n\nAlways make sure to respect copyright laws when downloading and using books from these sources. Libraries and educational institutions can also be valuable resources for accessing engineering textbooks legally.",
